# SOEN 357 Proto-type Palateventure

Welcome to the Palateventure prototype project! This repository contains both the front-end and back-end code for the project. In order to get started, please follow the instructions below:

## How to use:

1. Open a command terminal or powershell, and navigate to the front-end folder.
2. Make sure you have all the needed libraries installed by running the command below in the front-end directory:
npm install
3. Once all the libraries are installed, start the front-end server by typing the following command in the terminal:
npm start
4. To start the back-end server, change directory into the back-end folder and type the following command in the terminal:
nodemon index.js

## Accessing the Application
Once both the front-end and back-end servers are running, you should be able to access the Palateventure application by navigating to `http://localhost:3000/` in your web browser.

Happy Palateventuring!
